# pnpm Monorepo + React Native

This repo uses `node-linker=hoisted` (`.npmrc`). All packages hoist to the repo root `node_modules/`.

## Path Rules

All config files inside `apps/mobile/` must reference the **root** `node_modules/`, not the local one.

```
Repo root:          /snacky/
Mobile app:         /snacky/apps/mobile/
Root node_modules:  /snacky/node_modules/       ← packages live HERE
```

### Android Gradle (`apps/mobile/android/`)

- `settings.gradle`: `includeBuild("../../../node_modules/@react-native/gradle-plugin")`
- `app/build.gradle` react block: paths must use `../../../../node_modules/` (relative from `android/app/`)

```groovy
// ✅ GOOD — 4 levels up from android/app/ to repo root
react {
    root = file("../../../..")
    reactNativeDir = file("../../../../node_modules/react-native")
    codegenDir = file("../../../../node_modules/@react-native/codegen")
    cliFile = file("../../../../node_modules/react-native/cli.js")
}

// ❌ BAD — default paths assume node_modules at apps/mobile/
react {
    // root = file("../../")  ← WRONG for monorepo
}
```

### Metro Config (`metro.config.js`)

Must include root `node_modules` in `nodeModulesPaths` and `watchFolders`:

```js
const monorepoRoot = path.resolve(__dirname, '../..');
{
  watchFolders: [monorepoRoot],
  resolver: {
    nodeModulesPaths: [
      path.resolve(__dirname, 'node_modules'),
      path.resolve(monorepoRoot, 'node_modules'),  // ← root
    ],
    disableHierarchicalLookup: true,
  },
}
```

### Path Alias

Use `~/` prefix, NEVER `@/`. The `@` prefix conflicts with npm scoped packages (`@react-native/`, `@supabase/`, etc.) in Metro resolution.

```
✅  ~/shared/components/Foo   → babel module-resolver + tsconfig paths
❌  @/shared/components/Foo   → Metro confuses with npm scope
```

## Shared Packages (`packages/*`)

Shared workspace packages consumed by Metro must point `"main"` to source TypeScript, not `dist/`:

```json
{
  "main": "src/index.ts",
  "types": "src/index.ts"
}
```

Metro transpiles TypeScript directly. There is no build step for `@snacky/api-client` or `@snacky/shared-types` in the mobile dev workflow.
